            "title": "Recordati Acquires 13,050 Own Shares for Approximately EUR570,000",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>(Alliance News) - Recordati Spa announced on Tuesday that it acquired 13,050 of its own ordinary shares between December 17 and 19.</p><p></p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n\nThe shares were purchased at an average unit price of EUR48.3650, for a total consideration of EUR565,913.25.</p><p></p><p>\n\n\nFollowing these transactions, the company now holds a total of 4.7 million treasury shares, representing approximately 2.3% of its share capital.</p><p></p><p>\n\n\nRecordati's stock closed up 0.5% at EUR48.68 per share.</p><p></p><p>\n\n\nBy Antonio Di Giorgio, Alliance News reporter</p><p></p><p>\n\n\nComments and questions to redazione@alliancenews.com</p><p></p><p>\n\n\nCopyright 2025 Alliance News IS Italian Service Ltd. All rights reserved.</p></div>",
